‚úÖ PHASE 1: Install AWS CLI (only once per machine)
If already installed ‚Üí skip to Phase 2.

bash
Copy
Edit
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install
To verify installation:

bash
Copy
Edit
aws --version
‚úÖ PHASE 2: Configure AWS CLI
Go to AWS Console ‚Üí Search IAM ‚Üí Users

Select your username ‚Üí Security Credentials

Under Access keys, click ‚ÄúCreate access key‚Äù

Select Command Line Interface (CLI) ‚Üí Create
‚Üí Copy the Access Key ID and Secret Access Key

In terminal:

bash
Copy
Edit
aws configure
Then fill:

pgsql
Copy
Edit
AWS Access Key ID: <paste from AWS>
AWS Secret Access Key: <paste from AWS>
Default region: ap-south-1
Default output format: text
‚úÖ PHASE 3: Create and Manage S3 Bucket
üîπ Create Unique Bucket
bash
Copy
Edit
aws s3 mb s3://your-unique-bucket-name --region ap-south-1
Example:

bash
Copy
Edit
aws s3 mb s3://nimra-cloudlab-2907 --region ap-south-1
üîπ Upload File to Bucket
bash
Copy
Edit
aws s3 cp <local-filename> s3://your-unique-bucket-name/
Example:

bash
Copy
Edit
aws s3 cp index.html s3://nimra-cloudlab-2907/
‚úÖ PHASE 4: Create CloudFront Distribution
Go to AWS Console ‚Üí Search CloudFront ‚Üí Click Create Distribution

Origin domain: Choose the S3 bucket you just created

Origin access: Choose ‚ÄúOrigin access control (OAC)‚Äù

Create new OAC ‚Üí Give it a name ‚Üí Save

Leave default settings ‚Üí Click Create Distribution

‚úÖ PHASE 5: Fix Bucket Policy (to allow CloudFront access)
Go to S3 ‚Üí Select your bucket ‚Üí Go to Permissions

Click Bucket Policy ‚Üí Paste this:

json
Copy
Edit
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowCloudFrontAccessOnly",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "Service": "cloudfront.amazonaws.com"
      },
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::nimra-cloudlab-2907/*",
      "Condition": {
        "StringEquals": {
          "AWS:SourceArn": "arn:aws:cloudfront::<your-account-id>:distribution/<distribution-id>"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
Replace:

"arn:aws:s3:::nimra-cloudlab-2907/*" ‚Üí your bucket name

"arn:aws:cloudfront::...:distribution/..." ‚Üí your CloudFront distribution ARN (from CloudFront details page)

‚úÖ Save.

‚úÖ PHASE 6: Access Your File Publicly
Once the distribution is Deployed:

Copy the CloudFront domain URL (e.g., d123abc9.cloudfront.net)

Open in browser:

bash
Copy
Edit
https://d123abc9.cloudfront.net/index.html
‚úîÔ∏è Your uploaded file will now be visible publicly!

